The first pass shows several large main effects: older age and palbociclib are associated with longer PFS, while stage IV, ECOG performance status, brain metastases, PIK3CA mutation, HER2 positivity, high Ki-67, and weight loss are associated with shorter PFS. I’m now moving to adjusted models and treatment-by-biomarker interactions, because the treatment main effects are likely confounded by biomarker selection.
